poem:
The Shuttergleam

Hark, hobble-hush, ye nightward nomads: mind the shuttergleam that sighs;  
hush-snap!  
The silverfuzz will steal the spill, the filmfloss folds in tinny ties;  
clack-snap!  

Gather gossamer reels, grease the gears—wind spoolswirl till it rings;  
ring!  
Tether tape, braid the bulb, brace the back — braid brane for the bright-bell springs;  
ring.  

From the darkbox burst the Brimblejaw, brim-brum, blink-brella bold;  
whack!  
I raised a silver-saber, flashfork fang—snapcrunch!—took its teeth and told;  
smack!  

Home with humming harness, we carry darkmade dreams and reels of gold;  
beam!  
We hiss-hush, click-click, doff dust, dance the reelring—cheer the shutterbeam, bold.  
shutterbeam.
